    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1882-02-04T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1882-02-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="104"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d104">
                <head>No. 104.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Lowell</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Frelinghuysen</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1882-02-04">
                            <hi rend="italic">February</hi> 4, 1882</date>. (Received February
                        16.)</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 305.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to my dispatch No. 300, of the 30th
                    ultimo, I have the honor to inclose the copy of a letter which I received this
                    morning, in which Lord Granville states that the lord lieutenant of Ireland has
                    expressed regret that he cannot, consistently with his duty, order the release
                    of Mr. Denis Hayes O’Connor at present.</p>
                <p>I have, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>J. R. LOWELL.</signed>
                </closer>
                <frus:attachment>
                    <opener>
                        <seg rendition="#center">[Inclosure in No. 305.]</seg>
                    </opener>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">Lord <persName type="from">Granville</persName> to Mr.
                                <persName type="to">Lowell</persName>
                        </hi>.</head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Foreign Office</hi>
                            </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1882-02-02">
                                <hi rend="italic">February</hi> 2, 1882</date>.</dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: With reference to my letter of the 30th of
                        December last, I have been informed by Her Majesty’s secretary of state for
                        the home department that he did not fail to refer to the lord lieutenant of
                        Ireland your communication on the subject of Denis Hayes O’Connor, now in
                        custody under the protection of person and property (Ireland) act, 1881, but
                        that his excellency has expressed his regret that he cannot, consistently
                        with his duty, order the prisoner’s release at present.</p>
                    <p>I have, &amp;c.,</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>GRANVILLE.</signed>
                    </closer>
                </frus:attachment>
            </div>
        </body>
